# Metal RTX — Voxel Path Tracer

A real-time, hardware-ray-traced voxel tech demo for Apple-silicon Macs, written in
Swift with the Metal raytracing API. It renders a procedurally generated Minecraft-style
world with a full day/night sun cycle, emissive lanterns/glowstone, reflective and
refractive water, and a real-time path tracer with temporal + edge-avoiding à-trous
denoising.

![Daytime](docs/day.png)
![Night](docs/night.png)

## Features

- **Hardware ray tracing** via Metal `intersector<triangle_data, instancing>` on the GPU.
- **Voxel world** — procedurally generated terrain (FBM value-noise heightmap), trees,
  beaches, snow caps, and scattered light sources, greedy-meshed into triangles.
- **Instanced acceleration structures** — one triangle BLAS per chunk under an instanced
  TLAS (32 chunks, ~53k triangles).
- **Physically based path tracing** — diffuse (with sun next-event estimation), metals
  (GGX), and dielectric glass/water (Fresnel reflect/refract with transmission tint).
- **Animated, reflective water** — wave-perturbed normals with live roughness control.
- **Day/night sun cycle** — analytic sky with sunrise/sunset warmth, a sun disk, and a
  starfield at night; emissive blocks light the world after dark.
- **Real-time denoising** — temporal reprojection (world-space + normal + material
  validation) followed by a 3-iteration edge-avoiding à-trous filter, so the 1-spp image
  resolves to a clean result.
- **Free-fly camera** and a floating **HUD controls panel** for live tweaking.

## Requirements

- Apple-silicon Mac with a GPU that supports hardware ray tracing (**M3 or newer**
  recommended; requires `MTLDevice.supportsRaytracing`).
- **macOS 15** or newer.
- **Swift 6** toolchain (Xcode 16 / Swift 6).

## Build & Run

```sh
swift run -c release MetalRTX
```

The app opens a render window plus a floating **Controls** panel.

## Controls

| Input | Action |
| --- | --- |
| `W` `A` `S` `D` | Move horizontally |
| `Q` / `E` | Move down / up |
| `Space` / `Shift` | Move up / down |
| Mouse | Look (click the window to capture the cursor) |
| `Esc` | Release the mouse cursor |
| `Cmd-Q` | Quit |

The Controls panel exposes live sliders for **Time of Day**, **Exposure**,
**Sun Strength**, **Max Bounces**, and **Water Roughness**, plus a **Denoiser** toggle.

## Project layout

```
Sources/MetalRTX/
  main.swift, AppDelegate.swift, GameView.swift   App shell (programmatic AppKit)
  Renderer.swift, Camera.swift                    Render loop + camera
  Controls/ControlsPanel.swift                    Live HUD controls
  Metal/                                          Device setup, pipelines, shader library
  World/                                          Voxel storage, terrain, greedy mesher
  Shaders/                                         Metal shaders (path trace, denoise, sky…)
```

Shaders are compiled at runtime from the bundled `.metal` sources. They can be validated
offline with:

```sh
cat Sources/MetalRTX/Shaders/{Common,Sky,PathTrace,Denoise,Tonemap,Blit}.metal > /tmp/all.metal
xcrun -sdk macosx metal -std=metal3.2 -c /tmp/all.metal -o /dev/null
```